################################################################################
# Convolution tests
################################################################################

######################################
# Tests of convolution, explicitly.
######################################
The basic working version which can be used to test things out is 

   convolution_working_model.py

And convolves a Gaussian with another Gaussian.

Also, have 

   convolution_working_model_exp.py

which convolves an exponential with a Gaussian. A few things to note.

* I start with normalized functions and normalize the final convolved function.

* We want the convolving Gaussian to be normalized. 





#############################
# Using the CoGeNT utility.
#############################

Calls the CoGeNT convolve function on 4 ``spikes". 

   python testing_convolution2.py



Calls the CoGeNT convolve function on an exponential which acts as a 
faux WIMP signal.

   python testing_convolution3.py
